THE BEER-WARE ADDENDUM (Revision 42):

If this software saved you from mass data loss, spared you from explaining to
your boss why the backups weren't running, or simply made your Tuesday
afternoon slightly less miserable — you are morally (though not legally)
obligated to buy the maintainer a beer. Or a coffee. Or a mass-produced energy
drink of questionable nutritional value. Basically anything with caffeine or
alcohol. We're not picky.

If you are unable to deliver said beverage in person, a digital equivalent
via the project's sponsorship page is equally acceptable and significantly
less likely to arrive warm and flat.

If this software caused you problems, you may also send beer — the maintainer
will need it more than you do.
